1) We use the module that saves a log of a test. That log is used in a code review to make sure that there isn't any unnecessary queries on the page. In this case we add a sign to a db queries. That sign informs us about the db mode in which the query is executed: is it a slave mode or is it a master only mode. So we can see in the logs any 'SELECT' queries that occasionally is executed on the master server.
So we instead of this code in the `logQuery` method:
 
```
if ($this->db->enableLogging) {
    $rawSql = $this->getRawSql();
    Yii::info($rawSql, $category);
}
```

We write this code
 
```
if ($this->db->enableLogging) {
    $rawSql = $this->getRawSql();
    $message = $rawSql . ' '  . ($this->db->enableSlaves ? '(S)' : '(M)');
    \Yii::info($message, $category);
}
```

That is why we need to override `logQuery` method in the `\yii\db\Command()`
